
SQL DAY 4 - COUNT(), SUM(), AVG()

COUNT()

Used to count rows.

Example:

SELECT COUNT(*) FROM students;

--------------------------------

SUM()

Used to add values in a column.

Example:

SELECT SUM(marks) FROM students;

--------------------------------

AVG()

Used to find average value.

Example:

SELECT AVG(marks) FROM students;

--------------------------------

Memory Trick

COUNT() = Count rows

SUM() = Add values

AVG() = Average value

